---

## Rules

1. **Source:** Icons from Qure Figma design system node above. Export individual icons as SVG.
2. **Style:** Monochrome outline (stroke-based). Apply color via CSS/tokens.
3. **Consistency:** Use this set throughout. Do not mix with other icon libraries.

---

## Sizing

| Size | Dimensions | Use case |
|------|------------|----------|
| Small | 16×16px | Inline with text, inputs, compact controls |
| Medium | 20×20px | Buttons, nav items, list actions |
| Large | 24×24px | Prominent actions, headers, empty states |
| XLarge | 32×32px | Hero icons, feature highlights |

- **Min touch target:** 40×40px for icon-only buttons; size icon 20–24px and add padding.
- **Inline:** Match icon height to text line-height (e.g. 16px icon with 14px text).

---

## Coloring

Use **only** tokens from `design-system-tokens.mdc`. Implementation: `color: var(--text-base-default)` or `fill: currentColor` with `color` on parent. Never hardcode hex for icons.

| Scenario | Icon color |
|----------|------------|
| Primary action (CTA button) | `--text-brand-on-brand` |
| Secondary/ghost button | `--text-base-default` |
| Input leading/trailing | `--text-base-secondary` |
| Navigation, sidebar | `--text-base-default` or `--text-base-secondary` |
| Disabled control | `--text-disabled-default` |
| Alert/error | `--text-danger-default` |
| Success | `--text-success-default` |
| Warning | `--text-warning-default` |
| Active/selected nav item | `--text-brand-default` |

---

## Icon categories (reference)

- **Navigation:** Arrows, chevrons, home, menu, back, forward
- **Actions:** Search, filter, settings, edit, save, print, refresh
- **User:** Profile, users, lock, unlock, notifications
- **Files:** Document, folder, upload, download
- **Media:** Play, pause, volume, microphone, camera, chat
- **Status:** Info, warning, error, checkmark, star
- **Data:** Charts, analytics
- **Input:** Calendar, clock, checkbox, radio, toggle

---

## Implementation

### SVG usage
```tsx
<svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" strokeWidth="2" aria-hidden="true">
  <path d="..." />
</svg>
```
Use `currentColor` for stroke/fill so parent `color` controls the icon color.

### Icon-only buttons
- Add `aria-label` describing the action.
- Ensure min 40×40px click target.
- Use focus-visible ring.

---

## Implementation guidelines

- Always prefer the Qure icon set; check Figma before using any other source.
- Export icons as SVG from Figma; keep stroke/fill compatible with `currentColor`.
- A11y: `aria-label` for icon-only; `aria-hidden="true"` when decorative.
- Theme: Icons inherit from theme; no hardcoded light/dark colors.
- Do not invent variants; implement only what exists in Figma node 7809:18809.
